/* French case */ This section is entirely irrelevant. It says France opened a case against the MEK but finally "All charges including money laundering were dropped in 2014." It's wrong to insinuate that MEK did wrong in France & then state no wrong done.

/* Membership */ Deleting reference to MEK's numbers in Iraq. The MEK officially left Iraq in September 2016, as stated by the the group themselves, the UNHCR, and the U.S. State Dept. So this bit is actually outdated.

/* Paid advocacy */ Deleting section. None of the sources provided actually state that the MEK itself paid any of the officials mentioned. It's not appropriate to make charges against living persons. Further discussion will be added in Talk Page.

/* MEK in popular culture */ Deleted very biased section on media coverage of the MEK. Four of the 5 sources quoted were Iranian regime state media. The fifth was by a detractor of the group and it's not write to base an entire section on his comments.
